title <b>AgentAdapter</b> — Stage 1 trait, impls, and lifecycle types\n(Rust class diagram; <<trait>> = trait, <<struct>> = struct, ..|> = `impl Trait for Struct`)

' ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
' USER-FACING SURFACE (inherent impl on the trait object)
' ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

class "impl<R: Runtime> dyn AgentAdapter<R>" as DynImpl <<inherent>> #LightCyan {
  +for_type(t: AgentType) : Result<Arc<Self>, String>
  +start(self: Arc<Self>, app: AppHandle<R>, sid: String, cwd: PathBuf, state: AgentWatcherState) : Result<(), String>
  +stop(state: &AgentWatcherState, sid: &str) : bool
}

note right of DynImpl
  <b>One call hides all complexity.</b>
  Tauri command does:
  ` let adapter = <dyn AgentAdapter<Wry>>::for_type(t)?;`
  ` adapter.start(app, sid, cwd, state)?;`
end note

' ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
' TRAIT CONTRACT (the abstraction)
' ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

interface "AgentAdapter<R: tauri::Runtime>" as AgentAdapter <<trait>> {
  +agent_type(&self) : AgentType
  +status_source(&self, cwd: &Path, sid: &str) : StatusSource
  +parse_status(&self, sid: &str, raw: &str) : Result<ParsedStatus, String>
  +validate_transcript(&self, raw: &str) : Result<PathBuf, String>
  +tail_transcript(&self, app: AppHandle<R>, sid: String, cwd: Option<PathBuf>, path: PathBuf) : Result<TranscriptHandle, String>
}

note left of AgentAdapter
  <b>Send + Sync + 'static</b>
  Generic over `R: tauri::Runtime`
  so production (Wry) and tests
  (MockRuntime) share one trait.
  Each impl is generic too:
  `impl<R: Runtime> AgentAdapter<R> for X`
end note

DynImpl ..> AgentAdapter : exposes via inherent methods

